HEADWORD: Foremilk
<hw>Fore"milk`</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <fld>(Physiol.)</fld>
<def>The milk secreted just before, or directly after, the birth of a
child or of the young of an animal; colostrum.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Foremost</ent>⟦br⟧
